body:
@DaanHoogland @rhtyd @abhinandanprateek, even with this PR the problem keeps happening :(
How did you manage to reproduce this error?

In a VMware environment, this problem still happens (sometimes, which is even worse than if it would happen every single time). Interesting enough, after applying this PR and using only our XenServer clusters, the problem does not happen anymore (at least we were not able to reproduce it).

@karuturi 

For test_vm_life_cycle.test_08_migrate_vm, it looks like the test was run in a bad state for some reason:

jobresult : {errorcode : 431, errortext : u'Cannot migrate VM, VM is already presnt on this host, please specify valid destination host to migrate the VM'}

For test_deploy_vm_root_resize, it appears its XML config file references an OS type that doesn't exist.

@ustcweizhou @SudharmaJain : This PR got automatically closed while pushing the updated code. So created a new PR for this issue : 
https://github.com/apache/cloudstack/pull/2126

I have incorporated all the comments from this PR in the new PR. Please check the new PR.

Failed tests are not related to this PR.
Can some one please review this PR.
@borisstoyanov  Can you also trigger the Trillian.

@rhtyd Please add some integration tests for hard shutdown scenario. Also consider the case of starting a VM after stopping using hard shutdown.

The CS documentation should be updated to point to the relevant HV specific hard shutdown pros and cons.
 
PS: A similar thing was done in Cloudplatform but for the Destroy VM API. See if you would like to include that scenario as well in this PR or want it to be done separately.
